public abstract class DataFormula
extends java.lang.Object
implements DataValueChangedCallbackListener, Constants

A DataFormula describes a (possibly computed) attribute of a ResourceContext. DataFormulas are gotten from the corresponding context, by name. In general the name will be a toplevel static inner class of the context (which implies only one formula per type).
